	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=75042><span id= >marstorious</span></a><br><span id=notbold>14 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good [3.66]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>These items are used in little tradeskill chores in Abysmal.&nbsp;&nbsp;My advice is if you are already at or master at skill save a stack of this (Yes hard but is worth it).  These chores are basically a way of advancing in tradeskills without tedious farming.  Example: 1 Raw pale Nihilite = 2 Pale Nihilite + a recipe book.  Book supplies hints on higher and new tradeskills.  Turn in the stack to merchants:<br><br>Raw Pale Nihilite = Jeweler's<br>Taelosian Wheat = Baker's<br>Taelosian Stone = Fletcher's<br>Tealosian Tea Leaves = Brewer's<br>Aligned/Shimmering Ore = Smither's<br>Sample of Taelosian sludge = Alchemy<br>Muramite Etched Scales = Tailoring<br><br>Thus 1 Raw component yields 2. I am not sure how much tradeskill points are given for each recipe.<br><br>1 = 2 new components<br>20 new = 2 stacks(40 new components)<br>etc.etc.<br><br>Remember also that components can usually be given to both merchants.  I split between the 2 gave 1 stack to each merchant hence stack Looted components in 20's<br><br><br><em id=fs8>Edited, Mon Feb 16 21:53:27 2004</em></p>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
